questions on this topic from October last year, will [government] now commit to holding a full inquiry into this shabby practice?\"</p><p></p><p>Cable said the government would make sure \"we have proper enforcement procedure. You have listed more companies today, we will investigate them and it may well merit a more broadly based inquiry\".</p><p></p><p>He added that the employment agency standards inspectorate was investigating the individual cases. \"We will take enforcement action and if it proves to be a widespread practice then clearly there is a case for a more broadly based inquiry,\" Cable said.</p><p></p><p>The Recruitment &amp; Employment Confederation (REC), the trade body for the recruitment industry, said profiteering was \"a very serious allegation\" and asked Umunna to share any specific evidence he had to support the accusations.</p><p></p><p>Tom Hadley, director of policy and professional services at the REC, said: \"Let's be clear, employment agencies are not doing anything wrong by offering workers the opportunity to purchase accident insurance. It is a product that many other organisations offer to their members, including trade unions.</p><p></p><p>\"Personal accident cover can be appropriate for workers in high-risk sectors such as rail and construction, and may also cover them for accidents off-site that would prevent them from working, and provides them with an income whilst off work. By offering these benefits employment agencies are giving temporary workers the same kind of support as that enjoyed by permanent contracted employees.\"</p><p></p><p>But he said the REC had a code of conduct which required agencies to be open and transparent with workers. \"Anyone concerned can contact us, and we have a robust complaints process for handling agency workers' concerns and ensuring agencies are compliant with both the law and best practice.\"</p><p>In a statement, Blue Arrow said it took the welfare of employees very seriously, and that it did not believe anyone had taken out the insurance without fully understanding the benefits and the cost.</p><p></p><p>\"Many [workers] are employed in industrial situations where accidents can happen. We therefore believe that employees should be offered the opportunity to take out personal accident insurance.</p><p></p><p>\"It is important to stress that this insurance is offered, not sold. Our consultants are fully trained and regulated in line with the Financial Conduct Authority's guidelines and are not paid commission as personal accident insurance is not a sales initiative.\"</p>","headline":"Recruitment firms face mis-selling claims over workers' insurance","trailText":"Chuka Umunna, shadow business secretary, says several agencies sold personal accident policies to workers already covered by their employers' insurance","newspaperPageNumber":"26","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"theguardian.com","showInRelatedContent":"true","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3m5t5","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Money/Pix/pictures/2014/1/23/1390483391685/Network-Rail-workers-fixi-006.jpg","secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Money/Pix/pictures/2014/1/23/1390483391685/Network-Rail-workers-fixi-006.jpg","wordcount":"542","commentable":"true","internalContentCode":"427843652","allowUgc":"false","internalOctopusCode":"8596720","isPremoderated":"false","byline":"Hilary Osborne","newspaperEditionDate":"2014-01-24T00:00:00Z","internalPageCode":"2031485","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2014-01-26T13:25:02Z"},"rights":{"syndicatable":true,"subscriptionDatabases":true},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/money/2014/jan/23/recruitment-firms-mis-selling-claims-workers-insurance","apiUrl":"http://internal.content.guardianapis.com/money/2014/jan/23/recruitment-firms-mis-selling-claims-workers-insurance","tags":[{"id":"money/work-and-careers","webTitle":"Work & careers","type":"keyword","sectionId":"money","se